{
  "texts": [
    "The obtained P-value from Levene's test for homogeneity of variances equals 0.1458279957346559.",
    "As can be observed, the P-value for Levene's test is > 0.05, indicating homogeneity of variances across groups.",
    "Given the nature of the non-parametric distribution of the data, the Kruskal-Wallis test is utilized, which does not rely on these assumptions and is more robust in handling non-normally distributed data.",
    "In ANOVA, assumptions include normality and homogeneity of variances.",
    "Since the batch size violates the assumption of normality, ANOVA cannot be the most appropriate choice."
  ]
}